verses.roman:
ekeka janāre dui dui holnā dila
dadhi-ciḍā dugdha-ciḍā, duite bhijāila

synonyms: ekeka janāre—to each and every one of them; dui dui—two and two; holnā dila—earthen pots were supplied; dadhi-ciḍā—chipped rice with yogurt; dugdha-ciḍā—chipped rice with condensed milk; duite—in the two pots; bhijāila—were soaked.
translation: Each and every one of them was supplied two earthen pots-one of chipped rice soaked in yogurt and the other of chipped rice soaked in condensed milk.
